Iraq War: Jeremy Paxman faces being punished by the BBC after being judged to have violated the corporation's strict impartiality rules by writing an article for The Guardian in which he stated that Tony Blair's "lies" had led Britain to war with Iraq. (Daily Mail)Yemeni President Ali Abdullah Saleh scraps an offer to resign by the end of this year, as Islamist militants take control of a town in the south of the country. (Taiwan News)The European Commission is hit by a cyberattack. (Computerworld) (Europolitics)